headline: Problems Continue to Mount for Tesla. Is It Time to Sell the Stock?
summary: For instance, Tesla delivered only 1,429 vehicles in February in Germany -- which used to be its biggest European market -- compared to the more than 6,000 it delivered the prior year.  Consider that Model 3 sales are down 40% year to date in Germany, but Tesla was in the middle of a model changeover around this time last year, which would suggest easier comparisons for this year.  Recently, the company announced that it's bringing back highly subsidized financing, with its loans for new Model 3 orders offering annual percentage rates (APRs) of 0% or 0.99%.
